snippet.textDisplay:
By only clapping for the ones that you know, it makes it seem like the other people didn't make any impact in any of the projects that they worked on. They are on the memoriam for the OSCARS. They are all important people to the industry and should be respected. The actors and directors are not the only people that matter in making a movie.


Example: No one clapped for Barry Malkin because he's a film editor and no one knew him except that he edited almost all of Coppola's films specifically The Godfather Trilogy... so maybe he should be respected like he deserves to be.

snippet.textDisplay:
Since I've seen this a lot in the comments I'll answer two questions a lot of people seem to have.
1. Stan Lee died in 2018 and was honored at the 2019 Oscars.
2. Luke Perry was a TV actor so he'll be honored at the Emmy's not the Oscar's.

I understand why people are asking on both counts, though. RIP to both of them.
